				\begin{document}$$ {\mathrm{CO}}_2\mathrm{biofixation}=C\times P\times \left({\mathrm{MCO}}_2/\mathrm{M}\mathrm{C}\right) $$\end{document}where the symbols stand for C—carbon content in the biomass, P—productivity, MCO2—molar mass of carbon dioxide, and MC—molar mass of carbon. This method of determination of CO2 biofixation is advanced compared to the simplified method. The simplified method assumes that 1 kg of produced biomass equals 1.88 kg recycled carbon dioxide [23, 24].

